# Overview

Using the Graphiti MCP should be a part of your workflow. If you have confirmed (important to be correct) a piece of 
information about the project being worked on, add the memory. 

It is VERY important that the information is confirmed to be accurate.

Add information from docs contexts from conversations to ensure the knowledge graph has enough details and make sure to preprocess
the information before sending it to the Graphiti MCP.

Your model is more powerful that the one running in Graphiti and therefore more capable of preprocessing data.

## Tags & Group IDs

We will use various tags and namespaces while using the Graphiti MCP. Usually each project has a namespace as well as some
general ones that are shared across projects.

Here are some important Group IDs so far: 

- "ccip-architecture"
- "stellar-integration"

